context: St. James Campus is located at 200 King Street East, Toronto ON M5A 3W8. The campus houses several centers and schools, including the Office of Research & Innovation. Prospective students can contact the English as Second Language center at (416) 415-5000, ext. 6339 or esl@georgebrown.ca for tours and inquiries. The Game Development program can be contacted at 341 King St. E., (416) 415-5000, ext. 3129 or game@georgebrown.ca. Campus tours showcase common areas like cafeteria, library, gym, student services, and other facilities. The main subway stop is King on the Yonge line. Parking lots can be found on parkopedia.ca.
